While not a "religion" per se, Coryana does have Ten Commandments passed down from bronze age legal codes which form the basis of the modern Coryan sense of morality.

The first three of these commandments can be interpreted to be developments in an early form of the Coryan Utopian mindset:
1.Thou shalt respect your family, friends, and enemy
2. Thou shalt protect your nation and kind
3. Shalt take care of the surroundings and nature of everything
